I left out as much liquid from the filling as I could. I wonder if my pears were just a little too ripe. They weren\\u2019t soft, but they were juicy when I cut into them. Also, I made the caramel sauce the day before and warmed it up before adding it to the pie filling. Was it supposed to sit on top of the pear mixture? SO GOOD!!!! Here's what I did: I had picked some pears and needed to use them up, and they were really hard yet had a lot of flavor and were sweet. This was a benefit, because they kept some texture in the pie; I did not want mealy mushy pear goo in my pie. I actually cooked them down in the juices and sugar mix for about 5 or 10 minutes just to soften them up a bit and release some of the moisture. My mom tried to argue with me to put ALL the juices in the pie, but I followed the recipe, and it was fine (the caramel adds back to the filling so it's not dry at all.) The caramel was actually easy to make (BE CAREFUL), and it really elevates the pie. I wouldn't use just regular caramel here, because the salt balances it out so well. I used her pie crust recipe, too, and it was phenomenal, however I did swap out the vegetable shortening for lard (same amount) because I wanted it to be as old school as possible and lard is cheap! Let me tell yah, it worked like a dream. It was flaky and rich, just delicious. Just keep it all cold and you're good. If you think your dough mix is warming up just pop it into the freezer for 5 minutes while you're washing dishes or something. You can mix it for a bit, let it chill, mix some more, chill it again, etc. Just keep that lard and butter as cold as you can. I dusted the top of the pie crust (the one lining the pan bottom) with tapioca flour just in case it needed any help setting. I had consumed a bit of wine at this point, so I tried the lattice thing and I couldn't get it right, so I just rolled it out and put it on top, crimped the edges, and cut some decorative slits into the top of the pie crust and it worked out just fine! Cheers to all of you who got the lattice thing down, you're better than I am, lol. Another thing to keep in mind: you want to give a pie at least 4 or 5 hours to sit and set after you cook it, so that might be why some of the commenters had issues with runny pies. I will definitely make this pie again, and the salted caramel, and the pie dough! 3 great things came from me making this recipe, so that's really neat. query_text: What did Meghan McCain say about Levi Johnston and his responsibilities as a father?
ranked_results: [{"url": "https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/levi-johnston-palin-family-go-at-it-again-2009107/#article", "site": "usmagazine.com", "content": "{\"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"NewsArticle\", \"@id\": \"https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/levi-johnston-palin-family-go-at-it-again-2009107/#article\", \"mainEntityOfPage\": \"https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/levi-johnston-palin-family-go-at-it-again-2009107/\", \"publisher\": {\"@id\": \"https://www.usmagazine.com/#organization\"}, \"headline\": \"Levi Johnston, Palin Family Go at It Again\", \"datePublished\": \"2009-07-10T09:04:40-04:00\", \"dateModified\": \"2017-12-06T22:56:39-05:00\", \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Person\", \"name\": \"Us Weekly Staff\", \"url\": \"https://www.usmagazine.com/author/us-weekly-staff/\"}, \"description\": \"He says she resigned because of a lucrative book deal; her rep says he's \\\"honing his acting skills\\\"\", \"articleBody\": \"Levi Johnston and the Palin family are at it again.\\nIn an interview with the Associated Press, Johnson, the 19-year-old father of ex Bristol Palin's baby, said he believes Sarah Palin resigned as Alaska governor for financial reasons.\\nJohnston - who lived with the Palin family from early December to the second week in January - said he heard the governor several times say how nice it would be to take advantage of the lucrative deals that were being offered, including a reality show and a book.  \\nLook back at Sarah Palin's family on the campaign trail\\n"I think the big deal was the book.
